  UI helped with Illinois' pitch for Foxconn plant
Thu, 07/27/2017 - 7:00am | Ben Zigterman


CHAMPAIGN — Illinois made its case, but Wisconsin ended up being chosen by electronics manufacturing giant Foxconn for its new $10 billion factory expected to initially create 3,000 jobs.
University of Illinois officials were involved in Illinois' pitch, according to Ed Seidel, vice president for economic development and innovation.
 















